        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>N. Y. 1 June&#47;68<lb/>
            Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                My dear sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I am sorry to be so troublesome<lb/> to you but my wife has so little<lb/> faith in our coreligionists in this<lb/> country &#38; thinks so much of yr.<lb/> valued opinion that I am perforce<lb/> compelled to be troublesome<lb/></p>
            <p>I want to know if the Soap<lb/> <sic>advertized</sic> as enclosed is truly <hi rend="underline">Cosher</hi><lb/> as we want to use it for washing<lb/> cooking utensils &#38; dishes &#38; would<lb/> not buy any without it <sic>has</sic> your<lb/> approval.  Your reply will much<lb/> oblige.<lb/></p>
                <p>At last we are having<lb/> some fine weather could this<lb/> week it has been quite &#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
                <p>Religion is at a very low Ebb<lb/> here.  How is it with you<lb/>
                    The 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> day of Shebrath our<lb/> Synagogue was literally <hi rend="underline">empty</hi><lb/>
                    Do you intend to attend the<lb/> Sabbath observance meeting<lb/> &#91;&#63;&#93; fr. The Cong in 39<hi rend="sup">th</hi> fr<lb/> &#91;&#63;&#93; &#91;&#63;&#93;.<lb/>
            I presume yr. congregation<lb/> was invited to send delegates&#33;<lb/>
            If I can serve you in<lb/> anything here please make<lb/> me of use &#38; let me reciprocate<lb/> your kindness<lb/>
            With best wishes for yr<lb/> health &#38; happiness &#38; that of yr<lb/> good family<lb/></p>
                <p>I am my dr sr<lb/>
            yours Respy<lb/>
            J. Abrams<lb/></p>
            
        </body>
